Sample configs included in examples/ can be moved into cfg/
and then run via 'aug redis', etc. Edit as required for your env.

Alternatively, you can place your configs anywhere you'd like and
set the env_var AUGER_CFG=/path/to/your/configs.


BASH completion:

  function _augcomp () {
    augcfgs=$(aug -l|xargs)
    local word=${COMP_WORDS[COMP_CWORD]}
    COMPREPLY=($(compgen -W "$augcfgs" -- "${word}"))
  }
  complete -F _augcomp aug


ZSH completion:

_augprojects () {
  compadd $(aug -l)
}
compdef _augprojects aug

